sentences.english: Mason demands that Jack be turned over as well.
sentences.chinese: 梅森要求对方把杰克交出来。

sentences.english: Mason decides to interrogate Penticoff himself.
sentences.chinese: 梅森决定亲自审问彭蒂科夫。

sentences.english: Chapelle demands that Mason immediately end the situation at the facility.
sentences.chinese: 薛潘要求梅森立即终结拘留所的状况。

sentences.english: Mason suggests stress in the mothers in zoos might cause them to have babies that are less likely to survive.
sentences.chinese: 梅森认为动物园母象的压力可能导致小象成活率低。

sentences.english: Come into the warmth of the Fortnum and Mason tearoom .
sentences.chinese: 走进福特南和梅森商店暖融融的茶室。

sentences.english: Chris Metzen apologized for the mix-up at the L. A. Festival of Books.
sentences.chinese: 克里斯梅森为此还在洛杉矶图书节上向我道歉。

sentences.english: In total, only 49 Mersenne primes are known.
sentences.chinese: 目前总共只有49个已知的梅森质数。

sentences.english: Meanwhile, Mason has learned that Vanessa is cheating on him.
sentences.chinese: 同时梅森发现瓦内萨在欺骗他。

sentences.english: As the rest of the prospectus shows, lining the founders' pockets is all Groupon cares about.
sentences.chinese: 招股说明显示，梅森等人关心的只是自己的钱袋。

sentences.english: A Stream Parallel Algorithm of the Mersenne Prime Search Problem;
sentences.chinese: 梅森素数分布研究是数学中的一大难题。

sentences.english: When Mason asks what Tony wanted, Nina brushes him off.
sentences.chinese: 梅森问她，托尼需要什么，尼娜找个理由支吾了过去。

sentences.english: Suddenly, Mason and a group of agents surround them.
sentences.chinese: 忽然，梅森和一队探员包围了他们。

sentences.english: Jack is suspicious, and shoots Mason with a tranquilizer gun to knock him out.
sentences.chinese: 杰克感到怀疑，他用麻醉枪射击了梅森，把其弄昏了。

sentences.english: Mason and Lefkofsky decided to lay some people off.
sentences.chinese: 梅森和莱夫科夫斯基决定裁员。

sentences.english: Using a jar to stash spare change is a tried-and-true trick.
sentences.chinese: 用梅森罐来保存一些零钱是一种有效地方法。

sentences.english: Hear Devan and Mason talk about their love of home cooking.
sentences.chinese: 听听徳凡和梅森如何谈论他们最爱的家常菜。

definition: Brown (name)/Gordon Brown (1951-), UK politician, prime minister 2007-2010
Schröder (name)/Gerhard Schröder (1944-), German SPD politician, Chancellor 1998-2005
Carter (name)/James Earl (Jimmy) Carter (1924-), US Democrat politician, president 1977-1981
